## Key Guidance for Families

**Start here:** Call **1-800-642-3195** or **1-866-501-5656 (TTY)** to determine which program your loved one qualifies for. The tier they fall into depends entirely on their income relative to the Federal Poverty Level.

**Critical timing issue:** If your loved one qualifies for QMB, understand that coverage begins the month *after* MDHHS approves them — there's no going backward. For SLMB, coverage can reach back up to three months. For QI, coverage is limited to the calendar year of approval (with a January carve-out if approved in April or later). This matters for reimbursement planning.

**Automatic qualification:** If your loved one already receives SSI-related Medicaid, they automatically qualify for QMB without a separate application[4].

**Annual requirement:** QI beneficiaries must reapply every year, and approval is not guaranteed — it's first-come, first-served[5].

**Income verification:** Gather recent Social Security statements, pension documents, and any other income sources before calling, as MDHHS will need this to process the application[9].

